 also explain the observed (sub)millimeter and centimeter\nspectral energy distribution when we assume a constant, $\\sim$10$^{-4}$\n$M_{\\odot}\\,yr^{-1}$ mass inflow rate in this region. This explains how the\ninner 0.4 au disk is replenished with mass at a modest rate, such that it\nneither depletes nor accumulates significant masses over its short dynamic\ntimescale. Finally, we tentatively detect evidence of vertical dust settling in\nthe inner 10 au of the FU Ori disk, but confirmation requires more complete\nspectral sampling in the centimeter bands.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Aug 2019 09:15:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-06"}
